  "doc_id": "16185",
  "text": "A similar approach exists in the neural network literature, which uses a mechanism for altering the architecture of the neural network, called cascade-correlation [CITATION_1] . Cascade-correlation recruits new nodes in the neural network when the current architecture does not adequately capture the pattern of input and outputs. This has been used successfully to capture developmental stages [CITATION_2] and intermediate representations used for categorization [CITATION_3] . A flexible connectionist model for learning features using either mechanism would be very interesting and most likely could capture many of the feature learning results in this article; however, it would still have difficulty learning features whose images are transformed when instantiated in objects.",
